  "prompt": "What is it like to move from the UK to the USA?",
  "response": "Moving from the UK to the USA involves several significant changes:\n\n1. Cultural differences\n- More individualistic society in the US\n- Different social norms and communication styles\n- More diverse population\n- Less formal social interactions\n\n2. Legal/Immigration\n- Need for appropriate visa/work permit\n- Complex immigration processes\n- Different healthcare system\n- Must obtain Social Security Number\n\n3. Professional life\n- Different work culture\n- Typically less vacation time\n- More performance-driven workplace\n- Different employment laws\n\n4. Cost of living\n- Varies significantly by region\n- Generally lower housing costs outside major cities\n- Healthcare can be more expensive\n- Different tax system\n\n5. Daily life\n- Driving on right side of road\n- Imperial measurement system\n- Different electrical outlets\n- More car-dependent infrastructure\n\n6. Language\n- Similar language, but different slang/expressions\n- Spelling and pronunciation variations\n\n7. Education\n- Different academic system\n- More expensive higher education\n- Different grading methods\n\n8. Social aspects\n- More emphasis on networking\n- Different sports and entertainment cultures\n- Generally more extroverted society\n\nExperiences vary widely depending on individual circumstances, specific location, and personal adaptability.",
